title: For Sale:  WINCHESTER MODEL 70 375 H&H PRE WAR Rare
postcontent: Offered for sale is a Winchester Model 70 in 375 H&H, Sn 44097. By serial number this puts the year of manufacture of this rifle in 1941, only 875 Winchester Model 70's were made in this caliber before WW2. This Mdl 70 is one of the RARITIES of Model 70 collecting. Simply put the quality of the rifle is superlative. It feature Super Grade Sling Swivels, a factory red "Winchester" butt pad that is still pliable, express sights and a dark figured Walnut that might have made this rifle a special order? The rifle retains 98%-99% of it's original blued finish, a bright bore and the wood has some storage bruising which is consistent with it's age as all the pictures indicate. It also has a late 40's period Lyman Challenger All weather scope mounted on the rifle.

postcontent:
https://www.extreme-impact-ammo.com/index.php?l=product_detail&p=75













Buffalo Bore Ammo - .45 Auto Rim +P Ammo - 200 gr. Jacketed Hollow Point (1,200 fps/ M.E. 639 ft. lbs.) - 20 Round Box















You've been asking for a couple +P 45 AUTO RIM loads for a long time, so by popular demand, here they are. Both loads are using high quality Starline brass. We've also incorporated a flash suppressed powder so you can shoot in the dark without blinding yourself and this is important because over 95% of all civilian shootings in the USA occur in low light when the criminal element is at work. Both of these loads are the equivalent of +P+ 45 ACP ammo or as it is also known, 45 Super. These are very stout loads, but will not harm modern 45 ACP revolvers, nor will these loads harm any post war 45 ACP revolvers. Feel free to safely shoot these loads in any post war 45 ACP revolver that is in normal good operating condition.

Check out the below velocities fired from personal real world revolvers, NOT test barrels. You'll notice that the new S&W 4 inch Mt. Gun gives speeds almost as fast as the older S&W revolvers with 5.5 and 6.5 inch barrels. This is NOT a typo. It simply shows that the new S&W revolvers are made to much tighter tolerances than the older S&W revolvers and therefore give higher velocities per inch of barrel. Also, we are aware that the 1937 manufactured model 1917 we used as a test gun, (see below velocity chart) is not post war.

Item # 32B - 200gr. Jacketed Hollow Point bullet
S&W Mountain Gun, 4 inch bbl = 1197 fps
S&W Model 325 (scandium) 2.5 inch bbl = 1080 FPS
S&W Model 1917 (1937 production) 5.5 inch bbl = 1203 FPS
S&W 1955 Target (25-2) 6.5 inch bbl = 1249 FPS

Item # 32B was designed for expansion and massive terminal damage, with less than 1/2 the penetration of item # 32A in flesh and bone. Expect about 14 inches of penetration from this load on live flesh and bone.

For sale is my S&W M&P40c (compact). 

It has about 300 flawless rounds through it. 

It comes with one extra magazine ($50 value). 2 of the mags have a pinky rest and one is the flush-fitting. All three are 10-round mags. 

Installed is a Apex polymer trigger shoe. Note: This is not a trigger upgrade, but only the trigger shoe itself, as I did not like the factory, hinged trigger shoe. Still safe for carry and feels much better the mushy, hinged factory unit. This Apex trigger was also $50 after shipping.  The original is also included if you ever want to swap back to the factory unit, although I don't know why you would.

Also included is a Galco leather IWB holster. I have been carrying this pistol in this holster for about 18 months. Works great and very comfortable. 

As you can see from the pics, the gun is flawless. No scratches, gouges or holster wear whatsoever (I rarely remove from holster to keep it nice). 

The barrel has a brushed, satin stainless finish that I did myself. I do this to most of my pistols. You can see in the picture. Gives it a little flash, like a 1911, but nothing stupid. Rust is not an issue. These are stainless barrels.

title: For Sale:  Brand New Sig Sauer 556xi SWAT in 7.62x39!!
postcontent:
I’m selling my brand new Sig Sauer 556xi SWAT, chambered in 7.62x39. This is an awesome rifle that redefines modularity and combines the best aspects of the AR and AK platforms. Mine was purchased and upgraded less than 2 months ago and has only had precisely 5 shots fired from it (just sighting it in), so it is in absolutely perfect condition! I’m only selling it because my wife and I found out we’re pregnant. With twins. Which means that our budget priorities have suddenly and dramatically changed!!

Check out www.sigevolution.com/sig556xi for tons of info on the incredible number of upgrades and mods you can do with this platform. No other weapon lets you change out the caliber from 7.62x39 to 5.56 or 300BLK, or change the stock, magazines and controls with such ease. And the gas-piston system is recognized as being the most reliable operating system among military-style rifles. These guys thought of everything! This gun comes with a Swiss folding stock, cheek riser, ambidextrous controls, 16-inch barrel, upgraded 2-stage trigger, 3-position adjustable piston system, ergonomic grips and much more. 

I also dropped an extra $99 on an AAC Blackout Flash Hider that not only eliminates muzzle flash, but also serves as a the fast-attach base for AAC's high end silencers like the 762-SN!! So whether you shoot suppressed or loud, this rifle is ready for you! It’s a joy to shoot and will absolutely complete any true gunman’s collection.

List price on the 7.62x39 Sig 556xi SWAT is $1800.00, I bought mine 2 months ago for $1699.00 and spent another $99 on the flash hider. I’ve seen this rifle/caliber listed for as low as $1649.00. Because mine has 5 rounds through it I’m offering it for $1400, OBO. Cash only (of course), and I’d prefer not to ship it but if you have a dealer you work with and are willing to pay the shipping fees, we might be able to make that work too. I’m based in the Eugene, Oregon area, so any place within a reasonable drive works for me. We can meet halfway if you’re from further out. Any questions, please let me know by responding to this post or by calling Adam at REDACTED. Sorry, but absolutely no trades, thank you.
